I hope this is the right place to move some ideas and suggestions that I wrote in general yesterday:

1. A method to register Human and Authentic votes. A simple connect with discord and vote can lead to a lot of false / fake votes as there is no real cost in creating multiple Discord accounts. So voting should be two factor. Ie connect with discord and perhaps email or solve a captcha, enter a otp from email.
2. Concept of fractional down votes. A vote is a upvote. Fractional downvotes such as 1/10th of a down vote or 10 negative votes is a downvote could keep fake upvote abuse in check without downvotes itself being abused. 
3. All participants would get their own channels here for Q/A, comments, clarifications, updates etc.
4. Votes alone do not accurately reflect the viability of the projects. What if there would be a 3 tier system for votes: a) Invite a pool of people from VC circles to vote on projects - this will sort of indicate/imply to the community that the projects voted upon by the VC circle voters have possible value. b) Public vote by anyone via Discord and Twitter (via #hashtags such as #hyperSFvote<projectname>) and c) Vote by the actual investors in the hyperscalefund community by signing a vote with their metamask wallet. Each tier could have a some weight or multiplier associated so that algorithms could evaluate the most viable projects to be funded.

https://hyperscale.medium.com/whats-next-for-hyperscale-1326cfe4f7f5 - "Our past focus, the DAO race, unintentionally encourages groupthink. The distribution of votes is skewed towards the top. Most applications aren’t read because there’s no incentive to vote on the best projects." Possible solution: Have both list view and Card view as option, card view being the default. An icon and a short description of the project should be on the card. The card itself could show stats and few actions such as "More" to expand info, Vote to vote, "+" - a plus icon to add to compare list. Also one could have filters on top like on shopping carts to sort for most votes, newness etc. An example for card view: https://codepen.io/John2606/pen/yLzJLxp Also the first row of cards could be a totally random selection. The card view could be by default randomized or the first row could be randomized, that way we could take care of the skew and groupthink effect.
